The paper discusses the use of controlled English to improve semantic wikis, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and knowledge representation (KR). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper also touches upon database (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR) aspects of semantic wikis. Finally, the paper discusses user studies, which falls under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE).
